      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the title is now buried behind the image, it sounds like the image and title are competing for the same space, probably due to the lack of a clear stacking context. To resolve this, you can indeed use a media query to target the mobile view and adjust the styles accordingly. You could also add a `z-index` to your `.product-title` to ensure it stays on top. Here's an example:\n\n```css\n@media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {\n  .product-title {\n    margin-top: 10px;\n    z-index: 2;\n  }\n  .product-image-wrapper {\n    z-index: 1;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis will ensure that on screens smaller than 767 pixels, your title will have a top margin and a higher z-index, bringing it above the image. Remember to test the changes to make sure the title is visible and not too close to the image.",
