    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the layout is breaking apart, it sounds like the product image and title are both trying to stretch to their maximum width, causing the container to become unstable. To make the container more stable, you can set a max-width on the `.product-header` and ensure that both the image and title are contained within this width. You can also add some padding to the container to give it some breathing room. Here's an updated snippet:\n\n```css\n@media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {\n  .product-header {\n    max-width: 100%;\n    padding: 0 15px;\n  }\n  .product-image-wrapper {\n    max-width: 100%;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n  }\n  .product-title {\n    margin-top: 10px;\n    z-index: 2;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis will ensure that the `.product-header` doesn't exceed the width of its parent, and both the image and title will scale down nicely within this space. The padding on the `.product-header` will give some space on the sides, preventing the elements from squishing together. Test this out on your mobile device to see if the layout looks more stable and pleasing.",
      "source": "target",
